Borders.

Icons.

Buttons.

Small decorative accents.

Never use for large surfaces.

Usage

≤ 5%

---

## Secondary Accent

**Antique Gold**

```text
HEX: #B89255
```

Purpose

Hover states.

Focus rings.

Premium memberships.

Luxury highlights.

---

## Primary Text

**Charcoal**

```text
HEX: #2B2B2B
```

Purpose

Headings.

Primary body text.

Navigation.

Buttons.

Maximum readability.

---

## Secondary Text

**Stone Gray**

```text
HEX: #66615A
```

Purpose

Descriptions.

Captions.

Metadata.

Supporting content.

---

## Muted Text

**Ash Gray**

```text
HEX: #98938B
```

Purpose

Hints.

Disabled text.

Optional information.

---

# 5.4 Nature Palette

These colors exist only as supporting accents.

---

### Sage

```text
#8B9D83
```

Represents

Growth.

Balance.

Calm.

Applications

Leaves.

Icons.

Illustrations.

Success states.

---

### Olive

```text
#75805F
```

Used sparingly.

Supports floral illustrations.

---

### Moss

```text
#607054
```

Reserved for

Illustrations.

Background artwork.

Decorative graphics.

---

# 5.5 Floral Palette

Flowers should remain soft.

Never saturated.

---

Blush

```text
#EFD7D7
```

Ivory Rose

```text
#F8EFEA
```

Soft Peach

```text
#F4E2D2
```

Cream

```text
#FBF8F2
```

These colors should only appear in illustrations, photography, or decorative accents.

Never use them for buttons.

---

# 5.6 Celebration Palette

Reserved for wedding moments.

Not everyday UI.

Gold Light

```text
#D8BE84
```

Champagne

```text
#E7D8B6
```

Soft Candle

```text
#F7EFD8
```

Used only for:

Success stories.

Celebration pages.

Engagement.

Wedding timeline.

---

# 5.7 Functional Colors

Success

```text
#4F7A58
```

Warning

```text
#B68B38
```

Error

```text
#A54A4A
```

Info

```text
#5E819B
```

These colors should be slightly muted.

Avoid bright greens.

Avoid bright reds.

Avoid bright yellows.

---

# 5.8 Color Hierarchy

The interface should approximately follow:

```text
Warm Ivory

40%

Pearl White

20%

Charcoal

20%

Stone Gray

10%

Champagne Gold

5%

Natural Greens

3%

Celebration Colors

2%
```

Gold should never dominate.

White space should dominate.

---

# 5.9 Contrast Rules

Minimum WCAG AA.

Large text:

4.5 : 1

Body text:

7 : 1 preferred.

Gold should never be used for body text.

Light backgrounds should always use charcoal text.

---

# 5.10 Gradients

Gradients should be nearly invisible.

Preferred

```text
Warm Ivory

↓

Pearl White
```

or

```text
Morning Cream

↓

Soft Linen
```

Avoid

Rainbow gradients.

Purple gradients.

Blue gradients.

Tech gradients.

High contrast gradients.

---

# 5.11 Gold Rules

Gold represents craftsmanship.

Not wealth.

Never use:

Gold shadows.

Gold backgrounds.

Large gold buttons.

Gold typography blocks.

Use gold only for:

Icons.

Borders.

Premium indicators.

Small highlights.

Micro interactions.

---

# 5.12 Background Rules

Backgrounds should feel layered.

Example

```text
Layer 1

Warm Ivory

↓

Layer 2

Soft Linen Texture

↓

Layer 3

Light Shadow

↓

Layer 4

Ambient Glow

↓

Layer 5

Content
```

No flat white pages.

No busy backgrounds.

---

# 5.13 Component Colors

Buttons

Ivory + Gold

Primary CTA

Warm Gold

Secondary CTA

White with Gold Border

Inputs

White

Hover

Soft Linen

Disabled

Warm Gray

Cards

Pearl White

Hover

Soft Linen

Navigation

Pearl White

Footer

Warm Ivory

---

# 5.14 Seasonal Variations

The core palette remains unchanged.

Only decorative illustrations may adapt.

Spring

More greens.

Summer

Brighter sunlight.

Monsoon

Cooler ambient light.

Autumn

Slightly warmer gold.

Winter

Cream tones.

Users should barely notice these changes.

---

# 5.15 Color Anti-Patterns

Never use

Pure Black

Pure White

Bright Red

Neon Green

Electric Blue

Purple Gradients

Hot Pink

Cyber Cyan

Orange Alerts

Unless absolutely necessary for accessibility.

---

# 5.16 Accessibility Rules

Never communicate information using color alone.

Pair colors with:

Icons.

Labels.

Typography.

Patterns.

Motion.

Example

Verification

✓ icon

Green accent

Label

Not color alone.

---

# 5.17 Color Tokens

```css
--color-bg-primary

--color-bg-secondary

--color-surface

--color-card

--color-border

--color-gold

--color-gold-dark

--color-text

--color-text-secondary

--color-text-muted

--color-success

--color-warning

--color-error

--color-info

--color-sage

--color-olive

--color-blush

--color-cream
```

Never hardcode colors.

All components must consume tokens.

---

# 5.18 Color Usage Examples

Hero

Warm Ivory

↓

Typography

Charcoal

↓

CTA

Champagne Gold

↓

Decorative Flowers

Blush + Sage

---

Profile Card

Pearl White

↓

Charcoal Text

↓

Muted Metadata

↓

Gold Verification Badge

---

